HEADWORD: codlins-and-cream
<hw>codlins-and-cream</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a plant of Europe and Asia
(<spn>Epilobium hirsutum</spn>) having purplish-red flowers and hairy
stems and leaves; it was introduced into North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hairy willowherb, <spn>Epilobium
hirsutum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cod liver</ent>⟦br⟧
